@node "Introduction" "MathFX Manual: Introduction"
@next "Overview"
@prev "Main"
   Being a student, I was always looking for a good math plotting package
for the Amiga, in order to assist me in writing @{i}scientific projects@{ui} that
involve @{i}math, function@{ui} & @{i}data plotting@{ui}. 

   Being a UNIX user, I was always fond about what kind of programs that
this platform had to offer. @{i}PGPLOT@{ui} by Tim Pearson is a good example of such
a program. The only dissadvantage of this program was the lack of
versatility in terms of the ability to use the program inside other
applications.

   Hence @{b}@{i}MathFX@{ub}@{ui} was created to allow the user to produce professional graphs
either as @{i}stand-alone applications@{ui} or from inside @{i}big projects@{ui}.
@endnode

@node "Overview" "MathFX Manual: Overview"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Introduction"
  @{i}MathFX@{ui} is a library of @{i}C@{ui} functions for @{i}drawing graphs@{ui} on a variety of
@{i}graphics devices@{ui} using the @{b}@{i}Amiga@{ub}@{ui} personal computer. The only assumption made
about an @{i}output device@{ui} is that it is capable of displaying a line, so new
graphics devices may be added readily by writing a small number  of
@{i}device-dependent@{ui} routines. 

  The library is @{i}SAS/C@{ui} compatible and is accessible using the @{i}SAS/C@{ui}  linker
(@{i}slink@{ui}). The library was written in plain @{i}ANSI C@{ui} dialect (except of the
@{b}@{i}Amiga@{ub}@{ui} specific code), so it is possible to use the library with other @{b}@{i}Amiga@{ub}@{ui}
compilers that utilitize @{b}@{i}Amiga@{ub}@{ui} @{u}standard object files@{uu}, such as @{i}DICE C@{ui}.
 
  For most applications, the program can be @{i}device-independent@{ui}, and the
output can be directed to the appropriate @{i}graphics device@{ui} at @{i}run-time@{ui}.
However, for specialized applications, where the absolute size of a graph is
important, it is also possible to specify the plotting area in terms of
@{i}absolute coordinates (millimeters)@{ui}.
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "MathFX Manual: Requirements"
@next "Installation"
@prev "Overview"
  To use this software you need:
  
  - @{b}An Amiga personal computer :-)@{ub}
  - @{b}An ANSI C compliant compiler @{ub}(SAS/C, DICE, Sozobon, Manx,...)
    @{b}capable of using Amiga object files@{ub}
  - @{b}Kickstart v1.2 or later@{ub}
  - @{b}512K RAM.@{ub}
  
  Bigger @{i}MathFX @{ui}applications require @{u}more@{uu} memory, but @{u}1MB@{uu} memory will
  be enough even to the most complicated ones.

 NOTE: Although @{i}MathFX@{ui} was created to provide the @{i}C@{ui} language a means of
handling @{i}plots@{ui} &@{i} graphs@{ui} from a higher level, it doesn't mean that it cannot
be used with other languages that support @{b}@{i}calls to external functions@{ub}@{ui}. A few
examples: @{b}ACE Basic@{ub} (hello David!), @{b}Hisoft's@{ub} excellent @{b}Highspeed Pasca@{ub}l,
@{b}Amiga-E@{ub}, @{b}Oberon@{ub}, @{b}Modula-2@{ub} and @{b}assembly@{ub} (the ones I know that can!).
@endnode

@node "Installation" "MathFX Manual: Installation"
@prev "Requirements"
  @{b}To install this software:@{ub}
  
   Copy the library to your @{i}C@{ui} compiler @{i}link libraries directory@{ui}. Make sure,
when compiling, to @{i}link@{ui} your program with the @{i}MathFX@{ui} library and with the
@{i}apropriate math link libraries@{ui} (they are supplied with your C compiler
system).
    
    Note: @{i}MathFX@{ui} performs it's math calculations using @{i}32 bits@{ui}, so your
compiler's math link library must support the @{i}IEEE@{ui} math format.
@endnode

@node "Registration" "MathFX Manual: Registration Information"
@prev "Installation"
   @{i}MathFX@{ui} took me about a @{b}year's@{ub} time to develop. During development I had
to study maths REALLY HARD, in order to be able to provide the program with
the neccessary routines for plotting. @{i}Accuracy@{ui} was one of my prime
directives during development time; after all, I really need the software to
be @{i}precise@{ui} because I had to use it for my projects.

   As I said, I am a student (at the Chemistry Dept of the University of
Athens). Being a student is wonderful, on the one side. You're given the
chance to explore many wonderful things and to learn how to THINK right
about life. On the other side, it is difficult to get a job since you don't
have enough time to acomplish this task; none wants a student to his work
since he isn't yet a professional, but just a person that needs a part-time
job, just to make some cash for his living.

   If you are (or ever were) a student, you'll probably had experienced all
these. Since I've put a lot of work on getting this program working, I
require a small @{i}fee@{ui} for my efforts. These money will help me cover some of
my expenses (such as my bus tickets) and will also encourage me to develop
the program even further.

   I don't like crippled software or an awful lot of keyfiles hanging around
my system. Thus, @{i}MathFX @{ui}is @{u}not@{uu} crippled IN ANY WAY; however it is @{u}COMPLETELY
UNOPTIMIZED!@{uu} The program as it is, it is @{b}@{u}very slow@{ub}@{uu} (especially on
un-accelerated machines). 

   The @{i}registration fee@{ui} costs only @{b}@{u}$20@{ub}@{uu} @{i}(inc. P&P)@{ui}. When you register, you'll
get a @{u}personalized@{uu} version of the library @{u}OPTIMIZED@{uu} for the following
systems:

  @{b}68000, 68020, 68020+FPU, 68030, 68030+FPU, 68040FPU@{ub}
  Total 6 libraries!!!!!!!
  
   The optimized version is written at 75% in @{i}assembly@{ui} language (instead of
this one that is ompletely written in @{i}C@{ui}), it is @{i}smaller@{ui} and @{i}faster@{ui} (@{u}around
60% faster in displaying graphics and over 350% in parsing data and tables
for plotting@{uu}).

   If you live in @{b}@{i}Greece@{ub}@{ui}, you can contact me for registration information.
   
   I accept cheques, with the above amound, from the @{i}national@{ui}  bank of your
country. @{i}Personal@{ui} cheques are also accepted, but it will take @{u}longer@{uu} for
your program to arrive, since the cheque has to be validated first. Please
@{b}DON'T @{ub}send money; I cannot take the responsibility if the money is stolen.

   @{b}@{u}Please support shareware authors. The Amiga scene REALLY needs the
support of software authors. Don't push them to abandon the Amiga!@{ub}@{uu}

   @{b}KEEP THE AMIGA ALIVE! REGISTER TODAY!@{ub}

                @{"Registration Form" link "Form" 0}
@endnode

